00:10:37.690 --> 00:10:45.100
Laura Clifford Barney was
born in Cincinnati in 1879

00:10:45.100 --> 00:10:51.850
to wealthy Albert Clifford
Barney who was an industrialist

00:10:51.850 --> 00:10:59.090
and financier, who was the son of
a manufacturer of railway cars.

00:10:59.090 --> 00:11:06.920
Her mother was Alice Pike Barney, a
prominent artist, a philanthropist

00:11:06.920 --> 00:11:11.180
and the daughter of a
multi-millionaire entrepreneur.

00:11:11.180 --> 00:11:15.800
Alice became a civic and
social leader in Washington

00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:18.270
in the early twentieth century.

00:11:18.270 --> 00:11:26.160
Albert and Alice had two
daughters, Natalie and Laura.

00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:30.240
Laura who was born three
years after her sister.

00:11:30.240 --> 00:11:36.310
The family moved to
Washington D.C. in 1889.

00:11:36.310 --> 00:11:38.820
The sisters had the rich

00:11:38.820 --> 00:11:43.540
and privileged life
and grew up in luxury.

00:11:43.540 --> 00:11:49.170
The family's summer
vacation home had 26 rooms.

00:11:49.170 --> 00:11:53.950
They had governess
and private tutors.

00:11:53.950 --> 00:11:58.840
The two sisters were sent to a
private boarding school outside

00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:03.270
of Paris, and then back to the US.

00:12:03.270 --> 00:12:07.270
And the family attended
Episcopalian church.

00:12:07.270 --> 00:12:14.880
The characters of the two sisters
were different from an early age.

00:12:14.880 --> 00:12:20.740
Laura was the one who was diligent,
the student - a diligent student,

00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:28.430
rather shy, who always tried to
improve and had serious thoughts.

00:12:28.430 --> 00:12:33.020
From childhood, she
had the sense of duty.

00:12:33.020 --> 00:12:35.750
Natalie was the opposite.

00:12:35.750 --> 00:12:44.050
In 1900 when Laura had returned
to Paris to continue her education

00:12:44.050 --> 00:12:50.310
in dramatic arts, she attended a
meeting at the home of May Bolles,

00:12:50.310 --> 00:12:54.590
an American woman living in Paris.

00:12:54.590 --> 00:12:59.320
May Bolles was among the first
group of Westerners who had gone

00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:05.740 position:56%
to visit the head of the Bahai
faith Abdul Baha in Akka, Palestine,

00:13:05.740 --> 00:13:09.280
today's Israel, the year before.

00:13:09.280 --> 00:13:16.690
Abdul Baha was the son of the
prophet founder of the Bahai faith.

00:13:16.690 --> 00:13:21.180
Because of the time limitations
I will not talk about the history

00:13:21.180 --> 00:13:28.080 position:56%
of the Bahai faith, whose forerunner
was the Bab, its founder Baha Alla,

00:13:28.080 --> 00:13:33.460
who was born in Iran 200 years ago.

00:13:33.460 --> 00:13:39.020
And because of his teachings he
was exiled together with his family

00:13:39.020 --> 00:13:46.160
and was imprisoned in Baghdad,
Adrianople, Istanbul and lastly

00:13:46.160 --> 00:13:49.040
to the prison city of Akka.

00:13:50.070 --> 00:13:56.500
Soon after that meeting with May
Bolles in Paris Laura traveled

00:13:56.500 --> 00:14:02.970
with her cousin to Akka to meet
the spiritual leader from the East.

00:14:02.970 --> 00:14:07.070
After a long and difficult trip.

00:14:07.070 --> 00:14:09.820
After meeting Abdul Baha,

00:14:09.820 --> 00:14:14.620
she realized that those were the
teachings she had been waiting for

00:14:14.620 --> 00:14:19.640
and she became a believer
in the Bahai faith.

00:14:19.640 --> 00:14:24.420
Laura's attraction to this
new faith were most likely

00:14:24.420 --> 00:14:28.660
because of the principles
of equality between sexes

00:14:28.660 --> 00:14:35.230
and the belief in the oneness
of God and oneness of humanity.

00:14:36.610 --> 00:14:40.550
She returned to Akka
after a few months.

00:14:40.550 --> 00:14:45.720
On her second visit,
Abdul Baha asked her

00:14:45.720 --> 00:14:54.420
to accompany Abdul Fadl Gulpaygani
an Iranian scholar to the West.

00:14:58.220 --> 00:15:01.060
Abdul Faz was the most rooted

00:15:01.060 --> 00:15:07.130
and the greatest Bahai scholars
living in Egypt at that time.

00:15:07.130 --> 00:15:11.930
She accompanied him to Paris with
a translator and after a stay

00:15:11.930 --> 00:15:16.460
of three months she
accompanied him to the US.

00:15:16.460 --> 00:15:21.090
Laura and her mother
paid for his expenses.

00:15:21.090 --> 00:15:26.650
During his stay Laura deepened
her knowledge of this new faith

00:15:26.650 --> 00:15:29.250
and started learning Persian.

00:15:29.250 --> 00:15:36.540 position:56%
In Washington Alice Barney,
Laura's mother had become interested

00:15:36.540 --> 00:15:40.710
in the Bahai faith and its
teachings and held meetings

00:15:40.710 --> 00:15:43.380
at her home for Abdul Faz.

00:15:43.380 --> 00:15:47.050
She painted a portrait
of him which is now

00:15:47.050 --> 00:15:51.900
at the Smithsonian National
Museum of American Arts.

00:15:52.990 --> 00:15:59.170
There were always write ups about
the Barney family in the local

00:15:59.170 --> 00:16:04.730
and even the national newspapers
given their social status.

00:16:04.730 --> 00:16:13.220 position:56%
An article in the Washington Post of
March 1902 read "Ms. Laura Barney,

00:16:13.220 --> 00:16:16.570
who is a Bahai'st as
are other members

00:16:16.570 --> 00:16:19.440
of Alice Clifford Barney's family,

00:16:19.440 --> 00:16:26.340
says that at Akka one sees
demonstrated both in the family

00:16:26.340 --> 00:16:31.310
and the religious life the
harmony and love which is one

00:16:31.310 --> 00:16:36.660
of the pivotal principles of
the teachings of Bahai'ism".

00:16:36.660 --> 00:16:39.960
And sometimes the news they covered

00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:44.690
in the newspapers gave
incorrect information.

00:16:44.690 --> 00:16:50.290
Laura was never amused, but this
was what she had to tolerate.

00:16:52.050 --> 00:16:57.230
Gossip magazines printed
several untrue and false articles

00:16:57.230 --> 00:17:02.070
about Laura's mother
and made fun of Laura.

00:17:02.070 --> 00:17:06.860
Her father who cared about
people's opinion about his family

00:17:06.860 --> 00:17:11.600
and their social standing was
not happy to see the articles

00:17:11.600 --> 00:17:17.510
and he decided to close the house
where the meetings were held.

00:17:18.560 --> 00:17:22.680
Another incident that
made him furious was

00:17:22.680 --> 00:17:27.530
that the year before the news
of the publication of a book

00:17:27.530 --> 00:17:31.620
by Natalie which had reached him.

00:17:31.620 --> 00:17:39.410
Natalie, Laura's sister was
an author, poetess, a rebel

00:17:39.410 --> 00:17:46.510
and later held literally salons
in Paris for about 60 years.

00:17:46.510 --> 00:17:51.700 position:56%
She was openly gay and her published
book was about lesbian women

00:17:51.700 --> 00:17:56.750
with drawings done by her
mother, which caused much grief

00:17:56.750 --> 00:18:08.990
for the father who went to Europe
to collect all published copies.

00:18:08.990 --> 00:18:15.290
Albert's wife and his two daughters
were following unconventional

00:18:15.290 --> 00:18:21.970
lifestyles and was too
much on his health.

00:18:21.970 --> 00:18:26.340
He was outraged with
the news of his family

00:18:26.340 --> 00:18:31.730
and had the second heart
attack and died in 1902.

00:18:31.730 --> 00:18:37.470
The father left his wife
and two daughters a fortune.

00:18:37.470 --> 00:18:47.960
Laura returned several more times
to Akka between 1904 and 1906.

00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:52.160
And spent weeks and
sometimes months there.

00:18:52.160 --> 00:18:55.990
Posing questions to Abdul Baha.

00:18:55.990 --> 00:18:59.980
Laura was deepening her
knowledge of the Bahai teachings

00:18:59.980 --> 00:19:03.470
and asking deep philosophical
questions.

00:19:03.470 --> 00:19:10.930
In 1906 at the request
of Abdul Baha Laura

00:19:10.930 --> 00:19:17.730
who was only 27 years old
traveled to Iran, the birth place

00:19:17.730 --> 00:19:23.150
of her faith to meet
the Bahai's there.

00:19:23.150 --> 00:19:28.310
She was accompanied
by Hippolyte Dreyfus.

00:19:28.310 --> 00:19:31.230
Hippolyte Dreyfus was
the first French man

00:19:31.230 --> 00:19:34.910
from Paris who had become a Bahai.

00:19:34.910 --> 00:19:39.780
Hippolyte had studied law
and had a doctoral degree

00:19:39.780 --> 00:19:45.410
and was practicing before
the Paris Court of Appeals.

00:19:45.410 --> 00:19:52.920 position:56%
He later gave up his legal career to
devote himself to oriental studies,

00:19:52.920 --> 00:19:59.230
comparative religion and learning
Arabic and Persian intending

00:19:59.230 --> 00:20:01.950
to translate the Bahai writings.

00:20:03.720 --> 00:20:09.090
Laura also had the chaperone
and escort, a French Bahai lady

00:20:09.090 --> 00:20:13.310
who accompanied her on this trip.

00:20:13.310 --> 00:20:19.690
They first traveled to Ashgabat in
Turkmenistan where a Bahai House

00:20:19.690 --> 00:20:22.750
of Worship was being built.

00:20:22.750 --> 00:20:25.340
They met the Bahai's there.

00:20:27.370 --> 00:20:32.050
Then they continued on to Iran.

00:20:32.050 --> 00:20:36.440
She was the first Western
Bahai woman

00:20:36.440 --> 00:20:43.020
and Hippolyte the first
Western Bahai man to visit Iran.

00:20:43.020 --> 00:20:48.460
Their stay lasted over
five weeks and most

00:20:48.460 --> 00:20:54.840
of the cities they visited had
historical Bahai significance.

00:20:54.840 --> 00:21:00.880
In each city they met with
dignitaries, government officials,

00:21:00.880 --> 00:21:06.580
prominent people and many
of whom were Bahai's.

00:21:06.580 --> 00:21:12.890
Laura said that she was
delighted to meet the crowds.

